```{r plot}
library(ggplot2)
library(ggtext) 

colors=c("Anthemidinae"="#0597C7", "Non identified"= "#69b3a2", "Anacyclus sp."="grey", "Plantaginaceae"="#fee090", "Primulaceae"="#fc8d59","Plumerieae"="#009F36")
legend_text= c("*Anacyclus* spp.", "Anthemidinae","Non identified", "Plantaginaceae", "Plumerieae", "Primulaceae")

box_plot <- data %>%
  filter(coverage < 500) %>%
    ggplot( aes(x=reorder(sample, coverage, FUN = median,order=TRUE), y=coverage, fill=ID, alpha=ID)) + 
    geom_jitter(aes(colour =ID), size=0.2, alpha=0.4,position = "jitter") + 
    geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA)+ 
    scale_color_manual(values=colors) +
    scale_fill_manual(values=colors,labels = legend_text) +
    scale_alpha_manual(values=c(0.4,0.4,0.4,0.4,0.4,0.4)) +
    labs(y="Coverage", x = "Sample",title= "Coverage of the 442 nuclear makers per sample", fill = "Identification") +
    theme(
      text = element_text(family = 'Times'),
      legend.key=element_blank(),
      legend.title = element_text( size = 14),
      legend.text = element_markdown(),
      axis.text.x = element_text( size = 10, angle = 90, hjust = .5, vjust = .5, face = "plain"), #X axis names sizes
      axis.title = element_text(hjust = 0, size = 9),
      axis.title.x = element_text(size = rel(1.8), angle = 00), #x axis label
      axis.title.y = element_text(size = rel(1.8), angle = 90), #y axis label 
      panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
      panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "grey",size = 0.2),
      axis.ticks  = element_blank(),
      panel.background = element_blank(),
      plot.margin = margin(2, 2, 2, 2, "cm")
      
      )
     

# Add an arrow in the bottom right corner outside the plotting area
library(grid)
box_plot <- box_plot + annotation_custom(
  grob = linesGrob(arrow=arrow(type="open", ends="last", length=unit(3,"mm")), gp=gpar(col="black", lwd=1)), 
  xmin = 8.5, xmax = 25, ymin = -75, ymax = -75
)
box_plot <- box_plot + annotation_custom(
  grob = linesGrob(arrow=arrow(type="open", ends="last", length=unit(3,"mm")), gp=gpar(col="black", lwd=1)), 
  xmin = -3.3 , xmax = -3.3, ymin = 105, ymax = 320
)
# Turn off panel clipping
gt <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(box_plot))
gt$layout$clip[gt$layout$name == "panel"] <- "off"
```
